743
01:13:08,720 --> 01:13:10,551
# Se la dio con dos amigos

744
01:13:10,640 --> 01:13:13,791
# Dale a tu cuerpo alegria, Macarena...

745
01:13:13,880 --> 01:13:15,313
So? What do you think, then?

746
01:13:15,400 --> 01:13:18,039
I don't think anything. Why?

747
01:13:18,120 --> 01:13:19,633
Nothing.

748
01:13:19,720 --> 01:13:21,392
I was just wondering, that's all.

749
01:13:22,440 --> 01:13:26,149
There's nothing to wonder.
It's a business arrangement, that's all.

750
01:13:29,960 --> 01:13:32,235
And his ship sails tomorrow, like he said.

751
01:13:34,400 --> 01:13:35,753
Like he said.

752
01:13:47,720 --> 01:13:49,597
Good God.

753
01:13:49,680 --> 01:13:50,874
I can't drink all that.

754
01:13:50,960 --> 01:13:53,872
No, but I know a man who can.

755
01:14:00,960 --> 01:14:02,393
Cheers.

756
01:14:05,040 --> 01:14:07,429
Since when did you start smoking those?

757
01:14:07,520 --> 01:14:09,033
What happened to your roll-ups?

758
01:14:16,640 --> 01:14:18,915
Oh, Jesus. Make my next one a double.

759
01:14:21,360 --> 01:14:23,954
# When I was a young man

760
01:14:24,040 --> 01:14:26,270
# I used to dream of a maiden...

761
01:14:28,000 --> 01:14:29,194
That's my song.

762
01:14:29,320 --> 01:14:31,595
# With long soft hair

763
01:14:32,680 --> 01:14:35,194
# Blowing in the wind

764
01:14:38,120 --> 01:14:43,194
# Her laughing eyes
and loving arms would follow

765
01:14:45,760 --> 01:14:47,671
# When I'd sail around the world...

766
01:14:47,760 --> 01:14:50,035
Hey, Frankie. Hey, Frankie.

767
01:14:50,120 --> 01:14:55,240
I bet you all your trump cards
that you don't ask Catriona Murray to dance.

768
01:14:56,680 --> 01:15:00,195
# I'd ride down on a great white horse...

769
01:15:01,320 --> 01:15:04,437
If you do that, I'll get your mum up to dance.

770
01:15:05,720 --> 01:15:07,199
Deal?

771
01:15:08,880 --> 01:15:11,519
# I'd bring her laughter...

772
01:15:11,600 --> 01:15:12,794
Dance?

773
01:15:12,880 --> 01:15:15,235
# On a rainy day...

774
01:15:15,320 --> 01:15:17,197
I never dance.

775
01:15:18,280 --> 01:15:21,590
You'll have to this once.
Frankie's made another bet.

776
01:15:23,200 --> 01:15:26,351
You'd better watch him.
It's becoming a bit of a habit.

777
01:15:34,440 --> 01:15:39,514
# When I was a young girl,
I used to dream of a lover

778
01:15:42,760 --> 01:15:48,949
# Who'd be my shining knight
of strength one day

779
01:15:50,440 --> 01:15:55,468
# He'd take me to a castle in the heavens

780
01:15:58,640 --> 01:16:04,749
# And battle all my dragons on the way

781
01:16:05,640 --> 01:16:12,478
# And he'd ride down on a great white horse

782
01:16:13,800 --> 01:16:17,156
# He'd give me love

783
01:16:17,240 --> 01:16:20,550
# I'd been longing for

784
01:16:21,520 --> 01:16:25,308
# He'd bring me joy

785
01:16:25,400 --> 01:16:29,439
# And lasting peace

786
01:16:29,520 --> 01:16:33,399
# And on a great white horse

787
01:16:33,480 --> 01:16:36,233
# He'd ride away with me...

788
01:16:56,280 --> 01:16:59,670
Uno, dos, tres, cuatro.

789
01:16:59,960 --> 01:17:03,475
Uno, dos, tres, cuatro!

790
01:17:04,920 --> 01:17:06,797
I had a good time tonight.

791
01:17:09,880 --> 01:17:11,757
Don't sound so surprised.

792
01:17:14,200 --> 01:17:16,873
You are the best!

793
01:17:16,960 --> 01:17:18,837
He's got your eyes.

794
01:17:22,000 --> 01:17:23,513
They pull you.

795
01:17:24,520 --> 01:17:25,714
Right in.

796
01:17:25,800 --> 01:17:28,633
Uno, dos, tres, cuatro.

797
01:17:28,720 --> 01:17:30,597
I don't know what to say to that.

798
01:17:31,800 --> 01:17:33,756
Well, you don't have to say anything.

799
01:17:38,080 --> 01:17:39,752
You don't have to say nice things to me.

800
01:17:39,840 --> 01:17:41,717
I'm not paying you for that.

801
01:17:44,080 --> 01:17:45,957
So, why don't you want to hear them?

802
01:17:48,880 --> 01:17:50,757
What are you afraid of?

803
01:17:54,040 --> 01:17:55,917
Where did Marie find you?

804
01:17:57,880 --> 01:17:59,518
No.

805
01:18:00,520 --> 01:18:02,397
I thought we agreed: No history.

806
01:18:09,560 --> 01:18:11,437
Things have changed.

807
01:18:15,160 --> 01:18:16,639
Have they?

808
01:18:21,080 --> 01:18:25,278
What I find really difficult...

809
01:18:26,720 --> 01:18:28,597
to understand...

810
01:18:29,760 --> 01:18:31,239
is why?

811
01:18:33,480 --> 01:18:35,471
I told you why. Frankie made a bet.

812
01:18:35,560 --> 01:18:37,994
No, no, no, no, no.

813
01:18:38,080 --> 01:18:42,358
Why did he ever leave the two of you?

814
01:18:48,360 --> 01:18:50,590
He didn't leave us. I left him.

815
01:18:53,600 --> 01:18:57,070
One night I just picked Frankie up, and I left.

816
01:18:57,160 --> 01:19:00,197
And my mother came with me,
to make sure I never went back.

817
01:19:03,760 --> 01:19:05,557
And we've been leaving ever since.

818
01:19:05,640 --> 01:19:08,552
<i>Always ready in case he shows up.</i>

819
01:19:15,400 --> 01:19:19,029
Frankie wasn't born deaf.
It was a present from his daddy.

820
01:19:46,000 --> 01:19:49,470
Frankie's a very... very lucky boy.

821
01:19:52,680 --> 01:19:55,148
How do you figure that one out?

822
01:19:55,240 --> 01:19:57,913
I'm his mother, and I lie to him every single day.

823
01:19:58,000 --> 01:19:59,513
No.

824
01:20:01,160 --> 01:20:03,071
No, you protect him every single day.

825
01:20:08,360 --> 01:20:09,395
Do I?

826
01:20:16,720 --> 01:20:21,999
Every time I write one of those letters
I promise myself it'll be the last one.

827
01:20:23,760 --> 01:20:26,228
<i>I thought he'd lose interest, in time.</i>

828
01:20:27,320 --> 01:20:28,799
<i>Just stop</i>

829
01:20:31,640 --> 01:20:33,870
But see, if he hasn't written
for a couple of weeks,

830
01:20:33,960 --> 01:20:37,111
I'm the one egging him on,
telling him to hurry up and write.

831
01:20:39,920 --> 01:20:41,876
<i>It's the only way I can hear his voice.</i>

832
01:21:27,440 --> 01:21:28,793
<i>I'd better go.</i>

833
01:21:30,440 --> 01:21:31,873
I'm away first thing.

834
01:21:36,000 --> 01:21:37,592
Can I say goodbye?

835
01:21:37,680 --> 01:21:39,272
If you can wake him.

836
01:22:18,960 --> 01:22:20,359
Hey.

837
01:22:23,160 --> 01:22:25,628
You're coming back?

838
01:22:30,880 --> 01:22:32,916
I don't know, Frankie.

839
01:23:00,320 --> 01:23:01,389
Did you do this?

840
01:23:06,400 --> 01:23:08,834
Frankie, I can't take this. This... This is yours.

841
01:23:17,280 --> 01:23:19,157
I'd be honoured to take it.

842
01:23:21,600 --> 01:23:23,318
It's beautiful.

843
01:23:33,880 --> 01:23:35,757
Remember, Frankie.

844
01:23:37,080 --> 01:23:38,957
We're all connected.

845
01:26:51,080 --> 01:26:52,957
Lizzie, Lizzie.

846
01:27:02,000 --> 01:27:03,638
I've let myself go a wee bit. Sorry.

847
01:27:08,680 --> 01:27:10,511
It's been a long time.

848
01:27:15,480 --> 01:27:17,072
You're still beautiful.

849
01:27:18,240 --> 01:27:20,629
No, I'm not. I'm not beautiful.

850
01:27:21,680 --> 01:27:23,398
I'm sorry.

851
01:27:26,600 --> 01:27:28,431
I'm sorry, Lizzie.

852
01:27:29,480 --> 01:27:31,118
I'm sorry, Lizzie.

853
01:27:31,200 --> 01:27:33,270
Shush, Davey. Shush.

854
01:27:35,200 --> 01:27:37,919
It's all right. It's all right now.

855
01:27:39,560 --> 01:27:40,959
Don't cry.

856
01:27:46,720 --> 01:27:48,153
Where's Frankie?

857
01:27:48,240 --> 01:27:50,231
<i>He's at school.</i>

858
01:27:50,320 --> 01:27:53,073
He's nine now, nearly ten.

859
01:27:53,160 --> 01:27:54,673
Aye, I know.

860
01:27:57,360 --> 01:27:59,396
He's top at geography.

861
01:28:00,800 --> 01:28:02,677
I always knew he was clever.

862
01:28:05,360 --> 01:28:06,998
Must take that off you.

863
01:28:07,080 --> 01:28:10,789
I don't think so. You were the one
that could have gone to college.

864
01:28:43,440 --> 01:28:45,670
I want to see him, Lizzie.

865
01:28:45,760 --> 01:28:47,910
I've got a right to see him.

866
01:28:48,000 --> 01:28:50,116
<i>- Don't give me that.
- It's too late for fighting.</i>

867
01:28:50,200 --> 01:28:51,918
<i>Just let me see him.</i>

868
01:28:53,880 --> 01:28:55,757
I want him to know how sorry I am.

869
01:28:58,040 --> 01:28:59,439
He's my son.

870
01:28:59,520 --> 01:29:01,397
He's not your son. He's mine.

871
01:29:03,560 --> 01:29:05,790
You don't deserve him.

872
01:29:05,880 --> 01:29:08,599
You don't deserve his forgiveness.

873
01:29:11,080 --> 01:29:12,593
Christ.

874
01:29:15,000 --> 01:29:16,877
I made one mistake.

875
01:29:18,560 --> 01:29:21,677
One stupid fucking mistake,
and you made me pay.

876
01:29:21,760 --> 01:29:24,035
<i>You've made me pay, all right.</i>

877
01:29:25,160 --> 01:29:27,071
You're a bitch.

878
01:29:28,120 --> 01:29:31,078
<i>You're nothing but a bitch!</i>

879
01:29:32,520 --> 01:29:33,748
I want to see my son!

880
01:29:36,320 --> 01:29:37,639
<i>I've got a right!</i>

881
01:29:37,720 --> 01:29:39,233
I'm his father!

882
01:29:39,320 --> 01:29:40,912
<i>I've got rights!</i>

883
01:29:41,000 --> 01:29:43,833
I've got my rights! I'm his father!

884
01:29:43,920 --> 01:29:45,433
You're not his father!

885
01:29:45,520 --> 01:29:48,637
He's got a different father now, a real father.

886
01:29:48,720 --> 01:29:53,430
A kind, gentle man, who teaches him
to throw stones across the water.

887
01:29:53,520 --> 01:29:55,272
You could never be his father.

888
01:29:55,360 --> 01:29:57,237
I want to see my son!

889
01:29:57,320 --> 01:29:59,550
<i>- Davey, please, no, come on.
- I'm his father!</i>

890
01:29:59,640 --> 01:30:00,709
Davey, no, stop it.

891
01:30:00,800 --> 01:30:02,028
Nurse!

892
01:30:02,120 --> 01:30:04,031
<i>Nurse!</i>

893
01:30:04,160 --> 01:30:05,957
I want to see my son!

894
01:30:18,960 --> 01:30:20,837
Lizzie, wait a minute.

895
01:30:22,680 --> 01:30:25,558
Lizzie, Lizzie, please.

896
01:30:25,640 --> 01:30:27,949
He nearly killed us, Janet!

897
01:30:28,040 --> 01:30:30,031
I know. I know.

898
01:30:31,000 --> 01:30:32,956
He's only got a few days left.

899
01:30:33,040 --> 01:30:34,871
He can't touch you now.

900
01:30:35,720 --> 01:30:37,551
Let him die in peace.

901
01:30:38,320 --> 01:30:40,197
For your own sake.

902
01:31:13,520 --> 01:31:15,795
I want to talk to you. It's very important.

903
01:31:17,880 --> 01:31:19,757
I got a message today from your dad.

904
01:31:22,920 --> 01:31:25,195
He's not very well, Frankie.

905
01:31:25,280 --> 01:31:26,759
He's very, very sick.

906
01:31:29,400 --> 01:31:31,755
But he says he wants you to know he loves you.

907
01:31:33,760 --> 01:31:34,875
Very much.

908
01:32:06,400 --> 01:32:09,597
<i>Dear Da, I thought you'd like this drawing.</i>

909
01:32:09,680 --> 01:32:11,910
<i>I copied it from my book.</i>

910
01:32:12,000 --> 01:32:14,309
<i>Ma says you're not very well.</i>

911
01:32:14,400 --> 01:32:16,595
<i>I hope you feel better soon.</i>

912
01:32:16,680 --> 01:32:18,557
<i>Love from your son, Frankie.</i>

913
01:32:49,440 --> 01:32:51,317
<i>OK, call the crash team.</i>

914
01:32:54,120 --> 01:32:56,509
Please! What is wrong with him?

915
01:32:56,600 --> 01:32:58,636
Let's get the bed down. Come on.

916
01:32:59,680 --> 01:33:01,557
Mrs Morrison?

917
01:33:01,640 --> 01:33:05,076
It might be best if you went
and had a cup of tea just now.

918
01:33:05,160 --> 01:33:08,470
I'll send someone along to find you
as soon as we have any news.

919
01:33:09,520 --> 01:33:11,397
This is for my husband.

920
01:33:12,600 --> 01:33:13,919
It's from our son.

921
01:33:14,000 --> 01:33:15,513
Right.

922
01:33:20,040 --> 01:33:21,758
- Oh, Nurse, erm...
- Yes?

923
01:33:26,080 --> 01:33:27,513
Could you make sure he sees it?

924
01:33:27,600 --> 01:33:29,192
I'll make sure.

925
01:33:38,880 --> 01:33:42,395
<i>Davey Morrison
died peacefully after a long illness.</i>

926
01:33:42,480 --> 01:33:44,391
<i>Father to Frankie.</i>

927
01:34:15,680 --> 01:34:19,673
I know it's a terrible thing to say,
but Davey's finally done you a favour.

928
01:34:19,760 --> 01:34:21,432
It's over now.

929
01:34:25,120 --> 01:34:26,314
Marie?

930
01:34:26,400 --> 01:34:27,628
What?

931
01:34:28,640 --> 01:34:30,358
Who was he?

932
01:34:31,680 --> 01:34:33,352
My brother.

933
01:34:36,200 --> 01:34:37,872
Oh, right.

934
01:34:40,880 --> 01:34:42,757
I've got to go.

935
01:34:45,280 --> 01:34:47,510
- Where are you going?
- I'll see you after.

936
01:34:51,760 --> 01:34:53,352
<i>Do you want me to check the box?</i>

937
01:34:53,440 --> 01:34:55,317
<i>There won't be anything in it.</i>

938
01:34:55,400 --> 01:34:57,868
<i>It'll cost you to have your mail forwarded.</i>

939
01:34:57,960 --> 01:35:00,554
I'll check it for you, hen,
just to be on the safe side.

940
01:35:46,880 --> 01:35:49,235
<i>Thanks for the book.</i>

941
01:35:49,320 --> 01:35:52,153
<i>I've read it all the way through now twice.</i>

942
01:35:54,080 --> 01:35:55,752
<i>I took it into school.</i>

943
01:35:55,840 --> 01:35:57,353
<i>I know you won't mind.</i>

944
01:35:57,440 --> 01:35:59,396
<i>My teacher put it on the nature table.</i>

945
01:36:13,360 --> 01:36:15,828
<i>Miss Mackenzie gave me a gold star.</i>

946
01:36:15,920 --> 01:36:18,957
<i>I've got eight now. Catriona's got 20.</i>

947
01:36:19,040 --> 01:36:22,237
<i>Ricky's only got one, and it's not even gold.</i>

948
01:36:29,320 --> 01:36:30,435
<i>Guess what.</i>

949
01:36:30,520 --> 01:36:32,317
<i>I got into the football team.</i>

950
01:36:32,400 --> 01:36:35,358
<i>Well, the reserves. I'm playing on Saturday.</i>

951
01:36:35,440 --> 01:36:37,829
<i>And guess what else.</i>

952
01:36:37,920 --> 01:36:39,990
<i>I got one wrong in geography this week.</i>

953
01:36:43,960 --> 01:36:45,871
<i>Ma and I had a bit of a shock last week.</i>

954
01:36:47,000 --> 01:36:50,675
<i>My da - my real da - he's been sick.</i>

955
01:36:51,800 --> 01:36:54,155
<i>I think he's been sick for a long time.</i>

956
01:36:54,240 --> 01:36:55,832
<i>Ma never said anything.</i>

957
01:36:55,920 --> 01:36:57,433
<i>But I just knew.</i>

958
01:36:57,520 --> 01:37:00,751
<i>And last week, he died.</i>

959
01:37:00,840 --> 01:37:02,990
<i>I think ma's very sad, inside.</i>

960
01:37:03,080 --> 01:37:04,911
<i>But Marie says time's a great healer,</i>

961
01:37:05,000 --> 01:37:08,754
<i>and Ma's not to worry any more,
cos she's still got me.</i>

962
01:37:09,720 --> 01:37:12,234
<i>Anyway, I've got to go now. My tea's ready.</i>

963
01:37:12,320 --> 01:37:14,515
<i>I hope it's not chips.</i>

964
01:37:14,600 --> 01:37:16,477
<i>I've had them three times this week.</i>

965
01:37:17,880 --> 01:37:21,111
<i>Maybe you'll come and see us one more time.</i>

966
01:37:21,200 --> 01:37:23,270
<i>Maybe next time your ship docks.</i>

967
01:37:23,360 --> 01:37:25,237
<i>Your friend, Frankie.</i>

